// reaction-data.js
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CANONICAL SOURCE — hand-edited. Single source of truth for the
// reaction-tag taxonomy. Originally machine-generated by
// scripts/build-reaction-data.mjs, but after the chip-dedupe refactor
// (reactions.js now re-exports from THIS file) the generator pipeline
// went circular — both files describe the same data. So this file
// became the actual hand-edited source. The build script is retained
// for legacy reference but produces the same content it reads.
//
// Audit-tooling for batch edits lives in scripts/apply-vocab-audit.mjs
// (one-off transform; safe to extend for future vocabulary passes).
//
// Loaded as a classic content script (sets globalThis.__REACTION_DATA)
// AND imported as ESM by reactions.js for side effects (same globalThis
// assignment). Works in both because the file has no top-level
// import/export — only the IIFE wrapper containing the chip arrays.
//
// Schema per chip:
//   key       — unique slug
//   label     — visible chip text
//   polarity  — 'pos' | 'neu' | 'neg' (which rating shows it)
//   group     — feeling | pacing | craft | cast | story | takeaway
//   subgroup  — UI filter pill bucket within the group
//   weight    — scoring magnitude+sign (used by computeReactionOverlay)
//   keywords  — search synonyms
//   desc      — hover tooltip
//
// CURATED_REACTIONS = the 26 always-visible chips.
// EXTRA_REACTIONS   = the deep pool (search/dice/expander only).
// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

